The United States has expressed concern over the detention of Russian citizens who participated in rallies supporting Article 31 of the Russian Constitution, which guarantees the right of assembly. The US emphasizes the importance of protecting universal values such as freedom of expression and assembly, both in the Russian Constitution and international agreements. It believes that these freedoms are essential for a modern political system and economic modernization. The infringement on these rights goes against international norms and shared interests in fostering modernization. The US remains committed to supporting individuals in Russia and elsewhere who are working to protect and promote human rights and democratic values.